        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 10:11PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 1011 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles south of Fort Belknap, or 27 miles northwest of Zortman, moving
east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hays and Lodge Pole.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
